input_str: It’s a coincidence, but a rather piquant one, that yesterday, just a few hours after a blackboard work by Cy Twombly sold for $30 million in a Christie’s salesroom in London, Lucy Lippard took the stage in a Hilton in Midtown Manhattan and spoke about living modestly in the service of producing ideas. Nearly every line of Lippard’s acceptance speech for the College Art Association’s Distinguished Lifetime Achievement Award for Writing on Art was a gem; below are a few choice
